<br>
EDIT: Since Queen blade can't be MQ'd your only options to use the Golem Ball in trade are Spiroc Wingblade, Scales and Hand of the Maestro. Hand is rather easy to get, just need some Hate raids. Personally I'd consider trading the ball for Wingblade. Since scales are tradable most people/guilds who get extras usually sell them for hard plat. No idea of actual market value though, it has a lot to do about how much value each person puts on completing their epic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://members.fortunecity.com/burnkelethin/picz/banners/anibanner1.jpg><br><a href="http://members.fortunecity.com/burnkelethin/" target="_blank">BURN KELETHIN</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uanielact.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AnielaCT</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/14/02 1:11:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubadovk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>badovk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/02 3:39:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=397.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Camping Sev</span><hr size=1> I bought the MQ for the Ball of Golem for 5k. Couple guildies bought it for the same price. Fear raids aren't really something we do much anymore, so it seemed reasonable to me. I wouldn't have paid more, but one other friend bought it for 10k. I think that was more a case of him wanting it REALLY bad than it truely being worth that much.<br>
